{"title":"Kirai - flavored Android string formatting library","slug":"kirai-flavored-android-string-formatting-library","date":"2015-01-13T18:12:00.000Z","updated":"2019-07-03T22:51:02.813Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/kirai-flavored-android-string-formatting-library.json","excerpt":null,"covers":null,"content":"<h2 id=\"Overview\"><a href=\"#Overview\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Overview\"></a>Overview</h2><p>Recently I’ve developed and realased to Maven Central Repository <strong><a href=\"https://github.com/pwittchen/kirai/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Kirai</a></strong>, which is <strong>flavored Android string formatting library</strong>. Kirai means <em>phrase</em> in Swahili language. Project is inspired by <a href=\"https://github.com/square/phrase\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">phrase</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/polok/TaggerString\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">TaggerString</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/quiqueqs/BabushkaText\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">BabushkaText</a>. Kirai has fluent API similar to phrase with additional formatting similar to TaggerString and allows to add formatted pieces of text like BabushkaText. Development including writing Unit Tests took me about 2 days. Deployment and release to Maven Central Repository took me about 2 days as well. It was my first deployment, so it wasn’t so easy, but people from Sonatype are helpful, problems were solved very quickly and release went quite smooth.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Usage\"><a href=\"#Usage\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Usage\"></a>Usage</h2><p>Usage of the library is quite simple: </p>\n<figure class=\"highlight java\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br><span class=\"line\">9</span><br><span class=\"line\">10</span><br><span class=\"line\">11</span><br><span class=\"line\">12</span><br><span class=\"line\">13</span><br><span class=\"line\">14</span><br><span class=\"line\">15</span><br><span class=\"line\">16</span><br><span class=\"line\">17</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">// Basic Usage</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">CharSequence formatted = Kirai</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .from(<span class=\"string\">\"Hi &#123;first_name&#125;, your are &#123;age&#125; years old.\"</span>)</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .put(<span class=\"string\">\"first_name\"</span>, firstName)</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .put(<span class=\"string\">\"age\"</span>, age)</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .format();</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">// Flavored Usage</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">CharSequence formatted = Kirai</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .from(<span class=\"string\">\"Hi &#123;first_name&#125;, your are &#123;age&#125; years old.\"</span>)</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .put(Piece.put(<span class=\"string\">\"first_name\"</span>, firstName).bold().italic().big())</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .put(Piece.put(<span class=\"string\">\"age\"</span>, age).underline().color(<span class=\"string\">\"#FF0000\"</span>))</span><br><span class=\"line\">   .format();</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">textView.setText(formatted);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"Download\"><a href=\"#Download\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Download\"></a>Download</h2><p>You can depend on this library through Maven: </p>\n<figure class=\"highlight xml\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">dependency</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">groupId</span>&gt;</span>com.github.pwittchen.kirai<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">groupId</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">artifactId</span>&gt;</span>library<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">artifactId</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"tag\">&lt;<span class=\"name\">version</span>&gt;</span>1.0.0<span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">version</span>&gt;</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"tag\">&lt;/<span class=\"name\">dependency</span>&gt;</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<p>or through Gradle: </p>\n<figure class=\"highlight gradle\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">dependencies</span> &#123;</span><br><span class=\"line\">  <span class=\"keyword\">compile</span> <span class=\"string\">'com.github.pwittchen.kirai:library:1.0.0'</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"Open-source\"><a href=\"#Open-source\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Open-source\"></a>Open-source</h2><p>Library is open-source and available on GitHub at: <a href=\"https://github.com/pwittchen/kirai/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://github.com/pwittchen/kirai/</a> If you want to know more about library, check GitHub website of the project. Feel free to use it or fork it!</p>\n","more":"<h2 id=\"Overview\"><a href=\"#Overview\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Overview\"></a>Overview</h2><p>Recently I’ve developed and realased to Maven Central Reposi